tput; text does not require validating model judgment quality. System rejected because no real subprocess/OS/network is required to expose this state bug.","test_description":"Create round R0 on diff D0 with prior findings. Apply fixes to produce updated diff D1. Attempt finalize PASS without running new review round on D1; assert blocked with stale-review reason. Record fresh round R1 tied to D1, then re-attempt finalize; assert gate now evaluates based on R1 eligibility.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings, the flow emits an escalation outcome instead of PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure mode: state-machine/policy enforcement error across round counter + unresolved findings + terminal outcome emitter. Required setup: run loop state through max rounds with persistent MUST-FIX unresolved findings and verify final emitted outcome. Unit was considered, but failure is at interaction boundary between findings status, round-limit policy, and outcome module. Higher levels rejected: no real OS/network/subprocess required, no dependence on real AI output quality, and no required multi-agentic step chain in behavior text.","test_description":"Configure max review rounds N. Seed unresolved MUST-FIX finding that remains unresolved across N rounds. Execute loop to exhaustion. Assert terminal outcome is ESCALATION (or equivalent), never PASS, and escalation payload includes unresolved MUST-FIX context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
